her you are planning to attend Anthrocon or not, all the best during the current crisis.&nbsp; We are more than a mere conference or trade show. We are a community of friends and family.&nbsp; We hope that you are all safe and healthy.&nbsp; To those who have contracted the virus, wish you a speedy recovery.&nbsp; To those who may have lost someone, we send you our most heartfelt condolences. To those in the healthcare and other roles essential to our society, we take this moment to thank you for all of your work in this very stressful and tiring time.&nbsp; You are truly heroes, and you have our unwavering respect and gratitude.<br><br>Be safe and be well.<br><br>Your friends, </p><p class="">The Anthrocon Board of Directors and Staff</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Addendum to Anthrocon 2020 Refund Policy</title><category>News</category><dc:creator>Guest User</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2020 11:19:34 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.anthrocon.org/news/2020/3/25/addendum-to-anthrocon-2020-refund-policy</link><guid isPermaLink="false">59d2e7962994ca6597e2795c:59d2f8971f318d87163c5ecb:5e7b3d8f61495f27e2883cd0</guid><description><![CDATA[Due to the recent and ongoing issues caused by COVID-19, we are supplying 
